cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on device-to-device authentication using a fuzzy commitment scheme.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper uses natural gait as a means of authentication, which involves human movement and interaction with technology.
- cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses the use of a unique and natural characteristic (gait) for authentication, which could have implications for privacy and security in society.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper discusses ad-hoc device pairing and the establishment of identical keys for fingerprints generated at distinct locations on the same body.
